entries.player_reset_2: On second thought, I'd rather not.
entries.player_reset_1: On second thought, I'd rather not.
entries.npc_reset_2: I don't know if I should laugh or be disgusted. You could be the most timid mealy mouthed worm to cross my path in a long time.
entries.npc_reset_1: I don't know if I should laugh or be disgusted. You could be the most timid mealy mouthed worm to cross my path in a long time.
entries.waypoint_description_1: Kill the Imperial patrol leader and remove his shoulder pad.
entries.return_waypoint_description_2: Return to Vhaunda with news of your victory.
entries.return_waypoint_description_1: Return the shoulderpad to Vhaunda to prove your worth.
entries.player_reset: On second thought, I'd rather not.
entries.player_3_1: What is in it for me?
entries.player_1_1: What can I do to help?
entries.npc_work_2: Peila is waiting for you. It would reflect poorly on her if you made her wait.
entries.npc_work_1: I've told you all you need to know. Get moving.
entries.npc_reward_2: After Peila came to she filled me in on the details of your fight. You did well. It's too bad you're not one of us. Take this vibrolance as a gift.
entries.npc_reward_1: Well then, that's actually somewhat impressive. For an outworlder. This is going to look pretty good on my armor. Here's some cash for your trouble.
entries.npc_reset: I don't know if I should laugh or be disgusted. You could be the most timid mealy mouthed worm to cross my path in a long time.
entries.npc_noloc_2: I'm a little busy right now. Come back later.
entries.npc_noloc_1: I'm a little busy right now. Come back later.
entries.npc_failure_2: Hah! Who didn't see that one coming?
entries.npc_failure_1: Hah! Who didn't see that one coming?
entries.npc_breech_2: Hah, did you come to fight or beg for mercy?
entries.npc_breech_1: Situation is normal. I'm taking the patrol back to the outpost.
entries.npc_backtowork_2: Oh, by the way... good luck.
entries.npc_backtowork_1: That outworlder may not be entirely useless after all.
entries.npc_4_2: In our clan honor is everything. If you do not value yours, then why are you here, outlander?
entries.npc_4_1: Honor? The thrill of the hunt? If these do not motivate you I have nothing for you.
entries.npc_3_2: Aw, isn't that too bad. Maybe fighting isn't for you though? I hear the stables need a good cleaning, maybe that's more suited to your... er, abilities.
entries.npc_3_1: I don't know if I should laugh or be disgusted. You could be the most timid mealy mouthed worm to cross my path in a long time.
entries.npc_2_2: Well then, perhaps this outlander does have honor. Let's see how well they defend it. Peila will not be hard to find, let me draw you a map here on the ground.
entries.npc_2_1: Prove you are brave and loyal by bringing me the special shoulder pad from an Imperial patrol leader. My scouts will create a disturbance and lead a patrol to a location not far from here. You should be able to figure out the rest.
entries.npc_1_2: There are some of us who feel outlanders shouldn't be held to our standards. I'm not one of them. Neither is my friend Peila. She thinks you don't know your place and wants to fight a battle of honor with you. I think it would be amusing to watch. What are you going to do?
entries.npc_1_1: It's an unfortunate necessity that we have to have men on this planet at all. Men who don't follow orders however, are not tolerated. Perhaps you'd like to show your worth and get rid of a few?
entries.notyet: Outworlder, I don't think you cold perform the duties of our weakest man-slave. Come back when, or rather IF you are able to distinguish yourself further.
entries.notit_2: What is this? Stop wasting my time and do what I told you to do.
entries.notit_1: What is this? Stop wasting my time and do what I told you to do.
entries.next: I'm surprised, you actually did alright for yourself. I'll speak well of your ability.
entries.cant_work: I have a task for you when you're finished with what you're doing.
